ore actuator APIs directly without Docker, external services, environment variables, or system properties. The observed javac failures are Spring Boot 3.0 API changes, not missing setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment or system-property setup is required. Generated tests should target Spring Boot 3.0 APIs rather than the 2.6 APIs: for example, HTTP tracing moved from HttpTrace/HttpTraceEndpoint to HttpExchange/HttpExchangesEndpoint, several endpoint descriptor nested types were renamed, and constructors such as HealthEndpoint, EnvironmentEndpoint, and Sanitizer have changed signatures.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"spring-boot-actuator declares many optional integrations, including Jackson, Micrometer, servlet/webflux, data stores, messaging, and cache libraries. Tests that intentionally cover those integration-specific classes may need additional dependencies, but core actuator endpoint and model coverage is reachable without them.\",\n    \"Official application usage normally goes through spring-boot-starter-actuator, but adding the starter is not required for direct coverage of the org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-actuator artifact and could broaden the classpath beyond the failing compile issue.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_050deba44201f54b016a42a6e8136481968907094aa993f5e2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 861, "output": 649, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31718, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782752992508, "responseId": "resp_050deba44201f54b016a42a6e123848196b24dd34289c478d3"}}
